# Ticket Writing Conventions

## Title Format
`[Tool Type] [Project Name] - Ask summary`

Example: "AT Tooling - [Project Odysseus] Modify Autoreviewer to check spelling"

The 'Tool Type' basically refers to either 'RLS'/'HEX'/'Airtable' or 'Miscallaneous' if you can't decipher anything.

'Project Name' could be inferred from memory/slack conversation. 

It is definitely possible that you would not be able to infer these two things in some cases. If not, then simply summarize the title format based on the context and skip the placeholders.

## Description Template

```
## Summary
1-2 sentences. What is needed and why it matters.

## Ask Spec 
The ideal ask/end state as described by the reporter. If not provided
or ambiguous, note "Needs scoping."

## What is Being Blocked?
What step or process is stopped/hindered to complete the ask. If nothing is blocked, reply appropriately.

## Timeline 
When this needs to be done and why. If nothing is mentioned, reply appropriately.
```

## Priority Guide

| Priority | Level | When to use |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| Urgent (P0) | 1 | Experience-breaking; customer asked ASAP; can't do tasks right now |
| High (P1) | 2 | Blocking project start or key improvement; tight 24hr SLA |
| Medium (P2) | 3 | Important but not critical; ~3 days acceptable |
| Low (P3) | 4 | Wishlist items |

Default SLA is 24 hours. For <24hr SLA, the ticket must explain why
and the reporter should DM Arunavha Chanda, Dylan Pourkay, or oncall
AND Jordan Winawer.

## Key Principle
Filing the ticket is the priority. A ticket with full thread context
but missing some fields is better than no ticket. Always capture the
full conversation.

## Optional Slack↔Linear Linking
If the user explicitly asks BearBot to link conversation + ticket:
- Use Slack↔Linear sync/linking (thread connected to Linear issue)
- Post Linear ticket URL in the same Slack thread
- Treat this as optional; do not do it by default

## Default Status
- If ticket is assigned to an engineer at creation time, default state should be `Todo`
- If ticket is unassigned, keep default triage/backlog behavior
